article.description: — Kamaka Hepa had 13 points and 12 rebounds to guide Hawaii to a 79-55 victory over Hawaii Pacific on Saturday night.
article.headline: Hepa's double-double leads Hawaii over Hawaii Pacific 79-55
article.linkText: Hepa's double-double leads Hawaii over Hawaii Pacific 79-55
article.story: LAIE, Hawaii -- — Kamaka Hepa had 13 points and 12 rebounds to guide Hawaii to a 79-55 victory over Hawaii Pacific on Saturday night. Noel Coleman scored 13 and added five assists for the Rainbow Warriors (3-1). Harry Rouhliadeff shot 4 of 5 from the field to finish with 10 points. Trey Chapman led the way for the Sharks (0-1) with 10 points. Melo Sanchez added nine points, while Jalen Chandler scored eight. NEXT UP Hawaii hosts Sacramento State in its next matchup on Friday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
